<item>
            <title>[LU-9386] Add MDT to current MDS and add new OSS and OST</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9386</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On one of our clusters we are running version 2.1.3-2.6.32.  We are needing to expand the file system on new existing hardware - servers purchased at the same time for this future expansion.  Currently we have two OST&apos;s with 3x16TB LUNS each.  The MDT is 3TB.  We have outgrown this.  We want to add 4 OST&apos;s with 2x16TB LUNS each.  We will need to add an MDT as well.  I want to verify this plan and also make sure that adding an MDT to this version is possible and will increase available inodes?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL 6.8 server</environment>
        <key id="45652">LU-9386</key>
            <summary>Add MDT to current MDS and add new OSS and OST</summary>
                <type id="9" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/issuetypes/undefined.png">Question/Request</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="5" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/statuses/resolved.png" description="A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.">Resolved</status>
