                <updated>Wed, 21 Mar 2018 15:26:17 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Wed, 21 Mar 2018 15:26:17 +0000</resolved>
                                    <version>Lustre 2.1.3</version>
                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="224178" author="pjones" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2018 15:26:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that no further clarification is needed here&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="193058" author="pjones" created="Fri, 21 Apr 2017 17:25:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tony&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Probably the simplest option for outgrowing your MDT is to enlarge the size of the existing MDT rather than adding an extra MDT. As for upgrading, I would recommend that you upgrade first to a 2.5.x based release - that&apos;s the largest upgrade jump possible from 2.1.x, still supports RHEL 6.x servers and will provide you with options to move on to more current releases if/when you choose to do so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
